      "acceptanceCriteria": "SQA plan with full traceability, regression test suite covering hemolysis solver modules, and version-controlled releases required at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "SQA documentation exists but regression tests cover only 40% of hemolysis-relevant code paths; version control is present but release notes lack traceability to requirement changes. Achieved level 2 falls short of required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy tests on manufactured solutions for all governing equations including the power-law hemolysis transport equation; results must confirm design-order convergence.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy testing was performed for Navier-Stokes components but not for the hemolysis damage accumulation sub-model. Convergence rates for the scalar transport equation were not reported. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation or GCI-based discretization error quantification on hemolysis index QoI using at least three systematically refined meshes; GCI < 5% required.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh GCI study was completed; GCI for velocity field was 3.2% but GCI for hemolysis index reached 11.8% on the finest mesh pair, exceeding the 5% threshold. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match COU operating envelope (flow rate 3\u20136 L/min, speed 2400\u20133600 RPM) within stated tolerances; fluid properties must be characterised.",
      "rationale": "Experimental conditions covered 4 of 5 COU operating points; the highest-speed condition (3600 RPM, 3 L/min) was not replicated experimentally due to test rig limitations. Fluid viscosity was characterised but haematocrit variability was not controlled. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative agreement metric (e.g., NRMSE) between predicted and measured normalised index of haemolysis (NIH) must be below 15% across all tested operating points with uncertainty bounds reported.",
      "rationale": "NRMSE for NIH predictions ranged from 18% to 34% across tested operating points; predicted values consistently underestimated measured NIH at high shear conditions. Uncertainty bounds were reported but did not encompass experimental values at two operating points. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (NIH, shear stress distribution) must map directly to the COU decision metric (absolute hemolysis index below clinical threshold); traceability matrix required.",
      "rationale": "NIH is directly used as the COU decision metric and traceability is documented. However, the shear-exposure-time integral, a secondary QoI driving the power-law model, was validated only against literature correlations rather than direct measurement. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation must be performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under physiological blood analogue conditions at COU flow-speed combinations; no surrogate geometry acceptable at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Validation was conducted on the FDA benchmark pump geometry, which is appropriate, but blood analogue fluid (glycerol-water mixture) was used rather than porcine blood or equivalent. The hemolysis power-law coefficients were calibrated on a different pump family, introducing model-form extrapolation not assessed at the COU geometry. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence criteria must be demonstrated to be sufficiently tight that solver residual contributes less than 1% to total hemolysis index uncertainty; iterative error must be separated from discretization error.",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence was reported by residual drop of 10^-5 for continuity and momentum, but no separation of iterative error from discretization error was performed for the hemolysis scalar. Factor not assessed at the required level; flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent simulation by a second analyst using identical inputs must reproduce hemolysis index within 5%; analyst qualification records required.",
      "rationale": "No independent re-simulation was performed. Analyst qualification records were not provided. Use error is an unquantified epistemic gap at MRL 5 for this assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Systematic comparison of at least two hemolysis constitutive models (e.g., Giersiepen-Wurzinger vs. Taskin power-law) against experimental data at COU conditions; model-form uncertainty must be quantified and propagated to hemolysis index.",
      "rationale": "A single power-law hemolysis model (Taskin formulation) was used throughout; no alternative model forms were evaluated. Model-form uncertainty was not quantified. This is the largest identified epistemic gap at MRL 5 and a primary driver of the Not Accepted decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sensitivity analysis and Monte Carlo propagation of key input uncertainties (inlet velocity profile, fluid viscosity, pump rotational speed tolerance) to hemolysis index; 95% prediction intervals required.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed with 500 samples propagating inlet velocity and rotational speed uncertainty. Fluid viscosity was treated as deterministic. 95% prediction intervals were reported but did not account for haematocrit variability or temperature effects on blood rheology. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At least three independent experimental replicates per operating point with inter-replicate variability characterised; sample-to-sample haematocrit and donor variability must be reported.",
      "rationale": "Experimental data were drawn from a single published dataset (FDA benchmark study) with no independent replication at the COU operating points. Inter-replicate variability and donor variability were not characterised for the hemolysis measurements used in this assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal equivalency analysis mapping validation experiment input parameters to COU input parameters; any parameter outside the validated range must be flagged and its impact on hemolysis index bounded.",
      "rationale": "No formal equivalency analysis was performed. The validation experiment used a blood analogue at 37\u00b0C while the COU specifies porcine blood at 36\u201338\u00b0C. The pump speed range in validation (2000\u20133200 RPM) does not fully cover the COU upper bound (3600 RPM). Equivalency gaps are unquantified epistemic risks at MRL 5."
    }
